sentences: Yoo Si-ah (Korean: 유시아; born Yoo Yeon-joo on September 17, 1995), better known by her stage name YooA (유아) is a South Korean singer, and is a member of the girl group
She made her debut as a solo artist, with her first EP Bon Voyage, on September 7, 2020.
YooA was born Yoo Yeon-joo on September 17, 1995, in Seoul, South Korea, and legally changed her name to Yoo Si-ah.
On April 20, 2015, YooA debuted in the South Korean girl group
In August 2016, YooA took part in the Mnet dance TV show Hit The Stage with U-Kwon of Block B as her partner.
In November 2016, she debuted as a member of the Inkigayo project group, Sunny Girls, with the single, "Taxi".
In Summer 2017, YooA joined the reality show Idol Drama Operation Team.
In May 2018, YooA released the single "Morning Call".
In August 2019, it was confirmed that YooA would be taking part in Queendom as a member of Oh My Girl.
On September 7, 2020, YooA made her solo debut with the extended play Bon Voyage.
On September 15, 2020, YooA received her first music show trophy on The Show.
On September 25, 2020, YooA released an OST for the Netflix film Over The Moon.
Her older brother is Yoo Jun-sun, a dancer and choreographer under the well-known 1Million Dance Studio.
